Package subsetsum

Class SubsetSum

  • java.lang.Object
    • subsetsum.SubsetSum
  • public class SubsetSum
extends java.lang.Object
    SubsetSum class keeps track of the price of each item reading the CSV file with GroceriesFileReader class and also keeps track of the duration of the songs reading the data set in JSON format with MillionSongDataSubset class

      • findSubset

        public static java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> findSubset​(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Double> shoppingList,
                                                               double budget)
        The static method iterates through the shoppingList and creates a subset of this master list then checks if there are any numbers that are large but smaller than or equal to the sum. If so, the method adds it and and repeates the process until finds the number of subset whose sum is exactly the budget. Eventually, Generates a new subset from the existing subset and returns it
        Parameters:
        shoppingList - An ArrayList of shoppinList whose generic type is Double
        budget - A int value of the budget
        Returns:
        An ArrayList of generic type Double

      • findSubsetOfSongs

        public static java.util.ArrayList<SongEntry> findSubsetOfSongs​(java.util.ArrayList<SongEntry> songList,
                                                               double duration)
        The static method iterates through the songList and creates a subset of this master list then checks if there are any music durations that are large but smaller than or equal to the duration. If so, the method adds it and and repeats the process until finds the number of subset whose duration is exactly the the same as the argument. Eventually, Generates a new subset from the existing subset and returns it
        Parameters:
        songList - An ArrayList of songList whose generic type SongEntry
        duration - A double value of the musicDuration
        Returns:
        An ArrayList of generic type SongEntry
